OL,3,CJersey government defends living wage
OL,4,CU-turn
OL,6,FMinisters in Jersey are being
OL,7,Fcriticised for not meeting a
OL,8,Fcommitment to bring in a statutory
OL,9,Fliving wage, despite previously
OL,10,Fpledging to do so.
OL,12,FIn a report published by the Social
OL,13,FSecurity Minister, the government said
OL,14,Fintroducing the living wage was not
OL,15,F"feasible or desirable".
OL,17,FIt comes days after the charity
OL,18,FCaritas recommended the living wage in
OL,19,FJersey should become #13.41 per hour
OL,20,Fto reflect the current rate of
OL,21,Finflation of 10.1%.
